nsproxy tests
====================

This directory contains integration tests for nsproxy. The integration test
suite consists of three core components:

1. Target Server
   A ping-pong server (tcp_pingpong.py, udp_pingpong.py) listens on port 37777.
   It receives data from the client and sends a response back.

2. Proxy Servers
   Support for v2ray, sing-box, or shadowsocks-rust as proxy server.
   One proxy server instance listens on all 4 ports:
   - SOCKS5 on 31080 (no auth) and 31081 (auth)
   - HTTP on 38080 (no auth) and 38081 (auth)

3. Application
   The ping-pong client that runs inside a network namespace via nsproxy.
   Its traffic is captured by nsproxy and forwarded through the proxy server.


REQUIREMENTS
----------

 - v2ray
 - sing-box
 - shadowsocks-rust
 - iperf3
 - CoreDNS
 - Python3 with pytest

Dependencies should installed in $PATH


USAGE
----------

To run all tests:

   pytest -v tests/

Run the command above in the project root directory, not in 'tests/'

Note: nsproxy runs in verbose mode (`-vvv`) only when pytest is run with
verbose mode (`-v`).


ASAN AND UBSAN TESTING
----------------------

To compile with Address Sanitizer (ASan) and Undefined Behavior Sanitizer
(UBSan):

    cmake -S . -B build \
        -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo \
        -DCMAKE_C_FLAGS="-fsanitize=address,undefined -fno-omit-frame-pointer" \
        -DCMAKE_EXE_LINKER_FLAGS="-fsanitize=address,undefined"
    cmake --build build

Then run the tests as usual:

   pytest -v tests/


VALGRIND TESTING
----------------

To run tests with Valgrind memory checker, use the `--valgrind` option:

   pytest -v tests/ --valgrind

ASan is incompatible with Valgrind, don't use together. Here is the recommended
compile commands for Valgrind testing:

    cmake -S . -B build \
        -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo \
        -DCMAKE_C_FLAGS="-fno-omit-frame-pointer"
    cmake --build build
